Y2010N: The following minimum size limits (MSLs) were used to define a household agricultural holding: (i) the holding operates more than 0.1 mu (approximately 67 m2) of arable land or land under permanent crops and water surface of aquaculture at the end of year: (ii) the holding operates more than 0.1 mu of woodland and pasture at the end of the year; (iii) the holding keeps at least one large or medium livestock, such as cattle, horse, pig and sheep at the end of the year; (iv) the holding keeps at least 20 head of small animals, such as rabbits or poultry; (v) the income of the yearly sales of agricultural products, including self-consumption, exceeds RMB4 500; (vi) the income from providing agricultural services to other households or other entities exceeds RMB 500.

Y2020N: The following minimum size limits (MSLs) were used to define a household agricultural holding:  (i) the holding operates arable land, garden plot and aquaculture water surface cover with an area of 0.1 mu (approximately 67 m2) or more within the year; (ii) the holding operates woodland and pasture cover with an area of 1 mu or more within the year; (iii) the holding keeps at least one  large or medium livestock, such as cattle, horse, pig and sheep within the year; (iv) the holding keeps at least 20 heads of rabbits and other small animals and fowls  within the year; (v)the value of sold and self-produced agricultural products in the whole year exceeds 1000 RMB Yuan ; and (vi) the operating revenue from crop farming, forestry, livestock and aquaculture and fisheries service provided for other households exceeds 1000 RMB Yuan.

Y2010N: The agricultural holdings meeting at least one of the following thresholds were covered: 0.5 ha of UAA: arable land, permanent grass land, permanent crops; 0.1 ha of permanent outdoor crops included strawberries; 0.2 ha of outdoor fresh vegetables; 0.03 ha of fresh vegetables or flowers and ornamental plants under glass or other accessible protective cover; 0.1 ha of nurseries (except nurseries for forest trees); or ten bovines or 20 sheep over one year old or ten goats over one year old or five breeding sows or 50 other pigs or 1 000 poultry or 25 beehives. Y2000N: The census covered agricultural holdigns that met the following thresholds: one ha of UAA; 0.05 ha of flowers or greenhouses or nurseries; 0.1 hectares of specialized cultures; 0.2 ha of industrial crops or orchards; 0.5 ha under potatoes or under other crops extensively cultivated; one breeding bull; one cow; two head of cattle two years old; three pigs for fattening; one swine; six sheep or goats; ten female rabbits; 100 chickens or other fowls; ten beehives; or reported a certain livestock production for the 1998/99 agricultural seasons. The limits prescribed for the Autonomous Regions of the Azores and Madeira were slightly lower, bearing in mind particular regional features.

Y2010N: The census covered agricultural holding that met the threshold of 1 ha of UAA for the Mainland; however, the holdings had to fulfil a minimum area (or production) for certain specific crops or the existence  on the day of the interviewers visit, or production in the reference year  of livestock above the established threshold. For the Autonomous Regions, lower thresholds were applied: the minimum UAA had to be 0.1 ha.

Y2020N: The census covered agricultural holdings that met the threshold of 1 ha of UAA for the Mainland; however, the holdings had to fulfil a minimum area (or production) for certain specific crops or the existence  on the day of the interviewer's visit, or production in the reference year  of livestock above the established threshold. Y1970N: The census covered agricultural holdings and horticultural holdings. Agricultural holdings were all those reporting at least one of the following thresholds: 0.25 ha of cultivated land, including wood or forest land; 0.1 ha of land under vineyards, horticultural crops, small fruit, tobacco, medicinal plants and/or medium or small-sized fruit trees in compact plantation; one head of cattle; two head of pigs or sheep or goats; one head of pigs, sheep or goats, together with 15 head of poultry or 15 beehives; or 30 head of poultry or 30 beehives. No thresholds for horticultural holdings. Holdings consisting of ornamental parks or gardens, or raising or keeping horses not being used for agricultural purposes, were excluded.

Y1980N: Agricultural holdings were all those reporting at least one of the following thresholds: 0.25 ha of cultivated land, including wood or forest land; 0.1 ha of land under vineyards, horticultural crops, tobacco and fruit trees in compact plantation; one head of cattle; two head of pigs or sheep or goats; one head of pigs, sheep or goats, together with 15 head of poultry or 15 beehives; or 30 head of poultry or 30 beehives.

Y1990N: Agricultural holdings were all those reporting at least one of the following thresholds: 0.25 ha of cultivated land, including wood or forest land; 0.1 ha of special cultivations (i.e. berries, legumes, medicinal plants, vineyards, tobacco, orchards, mushroom cultivations); one head of any horses, ponies, mules or asses and 0.25 ha of cultivated land; one head of cattle; two head of pigs or sheep or goats; one head of pigs, sheep or goats, together with 15 head of poultry or 15 beehives; or 30 head of poultry or 30 beehives, or 100 rabbits. Y1950N: In Great Britain the census covered holdings with at least 0.4 ha of agricultural land. In Northern Ireland the census covered holdings with at least 0.1 ha of agricultural land.

Area: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
Y1960N: The census covered holdings with at least 0.4 ha of agricultural land. In England and Wales, 17 750 not statistically significant holdings were excluded. The census excluded woodland, osiers, and land under buildings, roads, yards, ponds.

Area: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
Y1970N: The census covered holdings that met the following thresholds: 26 standard man-days (smd). In England and Wales holdings with less than 26 smd were covered if they had 4.05 ha of land under crops and grass or one regular whole-time worker employed. In Northern Ireland holdings with less than 26 smd were covered if they had 0.4 ha of agricultural land or holdings with livestock returns from stock-keepers; and exluded holdings which were enterily let out seasonaly under conacre system and which temporarily became part of other farm business.

Area: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
Y1990N: The census excluded minor holdings. In England and Wales, a holding was classified as minor if all the following criteria were met: total area of less than six ha; no regular full-time farmer or worker; estimated annual lanour requirement was less than 100 days (of eight man/hours); greenhouse area was less than 0.01 ha; the occupier did not farm another holding. In Scotland, a minor holding was defines as one having a low level of agricultural economic activity. In Norther Ireland, minor holdings were those satisfying all of the following criteria: total area of land owned, or taken on long-term lease, was less than six ha; business size was less than one British Size Unit; no regular full-time worker other than the holder worked on the holding.

Area: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
Y2010N: The census covered holdings that met the following thresholds: 5 ha of UAA; 1 ha orchards/permanent crops; 0.5 ha vegetables grown in the open; 0.1 ha glasshouse for flowers, vegetables or fruit; ten head of cattle, 50 pigs or ten breeding sows; 20 sheep; 20 goats; 1 000 head of poultry; mushrooms. For Northern Ireland, the threshold was applied so that the population surveyed included all active farm businesses having one ha or more of farmed land, whether owned, leased or taken in conacre, and those with under one ha having any cattle, sheep or pigs or with significant poultry or horticultural activity.
